JIRA users have the ability to [configure project keys|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Configuring+Project+Keys]. If a user creates a project on a JIRA instance which allows non-default project keys (for example, project keys with numbers) then attempts to import this project on a JIRA instance which does not have the same regex, there are errors logged during the import which are non-useful: 

{code}
2010-12-03 15:09:34,178 JiraTaskExectionThread-11 ERROR jiraadmin 54574x281x1 1k7qw6w http://jiratrack:8080/secure/admin/ProjectImportSummary.jspa [jira.imports.project.DefaultProjectImportManager] An error occurred while tryin to create the project 'CPCRW0120' for project import. The import will be aborted. 
2010-12-03 15:09:34,178 JiraTaskExectionThread-11 ERROR jiraadmin 54574x281x1 1k7qw6w http://jiratrack:8080/secure/admin/ProjectImportSummary.jspa [jira.imports.project.DefaultProjectImportService] The import was aborted because there were too many errors. 
{code}

Because the project was named "CPCRW0120" (which is an invalid default project key due to the numbers), the project import failed. The expected error should be what is defined for the {{jira.projectkey.warning}} property in the {{jira-application.properties}} file, which by default is "You must specify a unique project key, at least 2 characters long, containing only uppercase letters." The request is for this warning to appear in the UI, and better yet, in the logs.

