A recent JIRA feature is the "leaving page" confirmation dialogue whenever a user navigates away from a page in which they have already entered some text. This is a sensible precaution. However, modern versions of Safari have a similar feature already built in. This means users must confirm leaving or closing the page twice (the JIRA provided dialogue appears first)

JIRA should not issue a confirmation under these browsers.

