I am upgrading from JIRA 4.1.2 to 4.2. We use MySQL in a shared environment. The default engine needs to be MyISAM. Since the InnoDB is the recommended engine, is there any way I can influence the restore operations to use this engine in the restore? If not now, perhaps a feature in the future?
{quote}

During an initial database configuration, install, or upgrade wizard, give customers the option to change the database engine for MySQL.
